K-12 School begins tomorrow!!!! Here are a few reminders as we begin the year.

*All PK-12 students will be provided masks. All students and staff will wear masks when not able to social distance.

*Students and staff will be required to wear masks on all BD & BDS transportation.

*All students and staff will be temperature checked each morning before entering the school building at 7:30. School buildings will remain locked until the designated time.

*Hand sanitizer will be available upon entering the building and in each classroom.

**Faculty and staff will continue to modify plans throughout the semester to maintain the school calendar..

For more specific information about the Bruning-Davenport reopening plans, please see our website for all additional information.

shared_text:
Damen Kugel
July 29 at 4:37 PM ·

I left the office today feeling defeated. I have countless things to get done before school opens and many new challenges to navigate. As I walked home, I heard a noise approaching from my rear. It was a senior student, Elijah.

He stopped in his ATV to visit with me. We talked about summer, returning to school, and his health. Before long with a smile, he offered me a ride in his ATV.

As we rode around town, we made small talk. As he pulled up to my house to drop me off, Elijah thanked me for helping out with his classes. He was appreciative of my efforts to keep him on track.

As I sat there in the ATV, my feeling of defeat had vanished. Instead, I gained a new perspective and vision.

Thank you Elijah for reminding me why I chose to be an educator and how fortunate I am to be a part of this great community.

post_text:
On April 1, Governor Pete Ricketts announced Nebraska’s eighth Directed Health Measure (DHM). As part of this DHM, Bruning-Davenport, along with all schools statewide are directed to operate without students in their buildings through May 31st. Extracurricular activities are also cancelled statewide as well.

Traditional graduation ceremonies are not going to be possible this May. We will be working to determine appropriate alternative methods to honor the Class of 2020, whether that be a ceremony at a later date or some other locally determined alternative graduation that complies with the guidance of health officials. Please be safe and take care of each other.

post_text: After consultation with our Health Department and other State and Local officials, it has been determined that all schools in the ESU 5 Region will be closed through Friday, May 1st, with the possibility of schools being closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. This decision will be re-evaluated as circumstances change, and another announcement will be made on April 22nd concerning the rest of the 2019-2020 school year. This is a precautionary public health measure; local health and school officials are monitoring the COVID-19 situation in Southeast Nebraska closely. School Superintendents met with Public Health Solutions and determined that this action would help prevent exposure to our area to flatten the curve and decrease the spread of disease.

Due to the COVID-19 Pandemic, Bruning-Davenport USD will be closed to students March 18, 2020 through March 31, 2020. This decision has been reached after much discussion and deliberation with state and local authorities. We plan to resume school on Wednesday, April 1st but may need to extend that closure based on the recommendations from health officials.

As always, our first priority is the safety and well-being of our students. We will continue to keep you informed should we need to extend the school closure. I have confidence that we have the best team in place to face this unprecedented challenge together. Thank you for your partnership and commitment to keeping our students and our community safe.

**NSAA has suspended all practices until March 30 and all NSAA activity competitions until Thursday, April 2.
